================================================================
PRACTICAL 9(b) - Automate Launching an Assistant Bot on a Keyboard Event
================================================================

DIFFICULTY: Medium

WHAT YOU WILL DO:
You will create a bot that stays in the background and launches 
(opens Notepad and types a greeting) whenever you press a specific 
keyboard shortcut (e.g., Ctrl + Alt + N).

--- STEP-BY-STEP INSTRUCTIONS ---

Step 1: Open UiPath Studio → New Project.
  - Name it: Practical_9b_KeyboardBot
  - Click Create

Step 2: From the Activities panel, drag a "Monitor Events" activity 
        into the Main sequence.
  - This activity keeps running in background and listens for events.

Step 3: Inside the Monitor Events activity, in the TRIGGER section:
  - Drag a "Hotkey Trigger" activity.
  - Key: select "n" from the dropdown
  - Modifiers: check both "Ctrl" AND "Alt" checkboxes
  - This means: trigger when user presses Ctrl + Alt + N

Step 4: In the ACTION section of Monitor Events:
  - Drag an "Open Application" activity.
    - Click "Indicate element on screen" or type the path directly:
    - FileName: "notepad.exe"
    - This opens Notepad when the hotkey is pressed.
  
  - After Open Application, drag "Type Into" activity.
    - Indicate element: click inside the Notepad text area.
    - Text: "Hello! The assistant bot is activated. Ready to help!"

  - Drag a "Message Box" at the end.
    - Text: "Bot launched successfully via keyboard shortcut!"

Step 5: Run (F5).
  - UiPath will appear to be doing nothing — it is waiting in the background.
  - Press Ctrl + Alt + N on your keyboard.
  - Notepad should open and the bot should type the message automatically.
  - The Message Box will appear.

Step 6: To stop the bot, click the Stop button in UiPath Studio.

ALTERNATIVE APPROACH (simpler — if Monitor Events is not available):
  Step A: Drag "Hotkey Trigger" directly into a "Trigger Scope" activity.
  Step B: Set the Key and Modifiers as above.
  Step C: In the body, add the Open Application + Type Into steps.

